In my opinion, "Shutter Island" is a fitting title. Take the generic definition of "shutter" for example:

Shutter- each of a pair of hinged panels fixed inside or outside a window that can be closed for security or privacy or to keep out light.

Similarly, Shutter Island is private, isolated, and secure.  Viewers constantly question what the staff of the island is hiding throughout the movie. We suspect something sinister and dark, and the patients are "shut inside", unable to leave.

Also, "shutter" sounds a lot like "shudder".
